---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
const repo = "https://github.com/SharathSPhD/PSALM";
const colab = "https://colab.research.google.com/github/SharathSPhD/PSALM/blob/main/notebooks";
---

<Base title="PSALM — Demos">
  <section>
    <h2>Run it yourself</h2>
    <p>
      Each notebook opens directly in Google Colab from the repository and runs end
      to end on a free GPU. They load the published model from Hugging Face, so there
      is nothing to train and nothing to download by hand.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Notebooks</h2>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="badge">colab</span>
        <h3>Minimal-pair scoring</h3>
        <p>Load an ELC-PSALM arm and score BLiMP-style minimal pairs by
        pseudo-log-likelihood — watch the model prefer the grammatical sentence.</p>
        <p><a href={`${colab}/01_minimal_pairs.ipynb`}>Open in Colab →</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="badge">colab</span>
        <h3>Śabdabodha pipeline</h3>
        <p>Turn a Sanskrit sentence into its typed Navya-Nyāya semantic graph and
        linearized Paribhāṣā string, the same dose that feeds arm D.</p>
        <p><a href={`${colab}/02_shabdabodha_pipeline.ipynb`}>Open in Colab →</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="badge">colab</span>
        <h3>Reproduce a result</h3>
        <p>Re-run the official zero-shot read-off on a published checkpoint and
        reproduce a number from the results page.</p>
        <p><a href={`${colab}/03_reproduce_eval.ipynb`}>Open in Colab →</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>From the command line</h2>
    <p>
      Everything the notebooks do is also a one-line script in the
      <a href={repo}>repository</a>: corpus assembly, tokenizer training, the
      two-stage curriculum, the official evaluation suite, and the leaderboard
      submission trainer. The README links each notebook with an open-in-Colab badge.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
